<p>
When the <code>os.path.join()</code> function receives a full file path, any path parts that come before the full path will be ignored.<sup><a id="fnr.2" class="footref" href="#fn.2" role="doc-backlink">2</a></sup>
This means that any attempt to use a relative path with <code>..</code> or <code>../</code> at the beginning will fail.
</p>
