<div id="outline-container-orgbcc2e53" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgbcc2e53"><span class="section-number-3">1.5.</span> root.</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-1-5">
<p>
Always check your privileges with <code>sudo -l</code>. In this case, running pip download as root can execute code when in the tar.gz format.
</p>

<p>
It is restricted to downloading from localhost:3000, so use the Gogs server.
</p>

<p>
It can download packages from the local Gogs server, which you can access. All you need to do is build a Python package that, for example, runs <code>cat /root/root.txt</code>.
</p>
